<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870701-0040 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Hovnanian Enterprises Inc.</HL><DD> 07/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HOV </IN><TEXT>   HOVNANIAN ENTERPRISES INC., Red Bank, N.J., predicted revenue of $320 million to $350 million and per-share earnings of $1.18 to $1.28 for its year ending Feb. 28, 1988. For the year ended Feb. 28, 1987, Hovnanian earned $18.5 million, or 88 cents a share, on revenue of $287.1 million. The fiscal 1987 per-share figure was adjusted to reflect a 2-for-1 stock split paid last April. For the first quarter, the home builder earned $5.7 million, or 27 cents a share, on revenue of $68.2 million, more than double the year-earlier quarter's earnings of $2.8 million, or 14 cents a share, on revenue of $54.7 million. </TEXT></DOC>